# shadcn/ui System Rules

This file defines how shadcn/ui is used within the application.

shadcn/ui is treated as a **primitives + system components layer**, not a design system of its own.

It must strictly consume the global design-token system.

---

# 1. Role of shadcn/ui

shadcn/ui is:

- a base component library (primitives)
- a composition foundation for shared/ui and features
- a consumer of design tokens (NOT a source of styling rules)

shadcn/ui is NOT:

- a design system
- a styling authority
- a place for feature-specific UI logic

Rule:
- shadcn defines structure, not design decisions

---

# 2. Token Dependency Rule (Critical)

All shadcn components must use semantic design tokens from the global system.

Allowed:
- bg-background
- text-foreground
- text-muted-foreground
- border-border
- bg-primary / destructive / secondary
- radius tokens (rounded-md, lg, xl, etc.)

Forbidden:
- hex colors
- arbitrary Tailwind colors outside token system
- feature-specific visual overrides that bypass tokens

Rule:
- shadcn components are token consumers only

---

# 3. Modification Rules

shadcn components must NOT be modified directly unless:

- fixing a library-level bug
- aligning with design token system compliance

Otherwise:

- extend via wrapper components
- use composition
- use className overrides only within token constraints

Rule:
- No direct redesign of shadcn internals

---

# 4. Wrapper vs Fork Rule

## Wrapper (preferred)
Use when:
- behavior remains the same
- only visual adjustments or composition changes are needed
- reuse is still valid across system

## Fork (discouraged)
Only allowed when:
- component purpose fundamentally changes
- abstraction no longer matches original intent

Rule:
- 80% similarity → wrapper
- structural change → reconsider design, not duplication

---

# 5. Composition Rules

- shadcn components must be composed, not duplicated
- do not recreate shadcn components with slight differences
- extend via shared/ui when abstraction is needed

Rule:
- duplication of shadcn components is a system violation

---

# 6. Variants System (cva usage)

- any multi-state shadcn-based component must use cva
- avoid ternary className styling for state logic
- variants must remain co-located and predictable

Rule:
- visual state logic must be centralized

---

# 7. Styling Constraints

- Tailwind is allowed only within token system constraints
- no arbitrary styling outside semantic tokens
- no per-feature styling logic inside shadcn layer

Rule:
- shadcn styling must remain system-consistent

---

# 8. Dependency Rules

shadcn/ui layer:

- must NOT import from:
  - features/*
  - shared/ui
  - application logic

Allowed:
- internal shadcn composition only

Rule:
- shadcn is the lowest UI layer and must remain isolated

---

# 9. Stability Rule

- shadcn components are high-stability primitives
- changes must be intentional and system-wide
- frequent modifications indicate architectural drift

Rule:
- shadcn changes must be justified at system level

---

# 10. Anti-Patterns

Forbidden:

- duplicating shadcn components with minor visual changes
- bypassing design tokens with arbitrary values
- embedding feature logic into primitives
- uncontrolled forks of base components
- creating parallel versions of existing primitives

---

# 11. System Role Summary

shadcn/ui is:

- a controlled primitive system
- a token-consumer layer
- a foundation for composition

It is NOT:

- a design system
- a feature layer
- a styling playground

---

# 12. System Guarantee

If respected correctly, this ensures:

- consistent UI primitives across the system
- strict token-driven design alignment
- controlled component evolution
- no primitive duplication or fragmentation